Date: Wed, 19 Nov 1997 16:40:39 -0700
From: Hal Nash <HNASH@wwcc.cc.wy.us>

As mentioned below, climatic factors have contributed to the increase in
tuberculosis in Indonesia. While most of the attention given to El Nino
Southern Oscillation is its eastern Pacific impact on South, Central, and
North America, let it be known that the "flip side" of ENSO is drought in
the western Pacific. We should not overlook the concurrent impacts of this
major influencing environmental force.
--
Hal B. Nash
Assistant Professor of Biology
Western Wyoming College
Rock Springs, WY 82902
hnash@wwcc.cc.wy.us

